    "name": "FLO (119)",
    "profile": "Flo (stylised in uppercase) is a British girl group from London consisting of members Jorja Douglas, Stella Quaresma, and Renée Downer. \r\nThe group formed in 2019 and signed to Island Records. The trio released their debut single \"Cardboard Box\", which gained popularity on social media.\r\nThe single was featured on their extended play, The Lead (2022). The success of their extended play led the group to receive the 2023 Brit Award for Rising Star, becoming the first all female group to win the award.",
